{"build_type":"library","description":"Return the default row budget for a recursive filesystem-subtree dump: the maximum number of entry rows the subtree tool emits before it STOPS descending and reports output_budget_exceeded (a LOUD structured truncation, not a silent 120s black-box). A deterministic COUNT budget (not a wall-clock timeout) keeps the verdict reproducible (CAS/diff) and is the right lever — the v2 perf work removed TIME as the limit, leaving output VOLUME as the wall. Larger than the one-directory listing budget because a whole subtree legitimately holds more rows. Defined as a function (lowering ignores global initializers) so the limit has one source of truth. Reused by emit_filesystem_tree_flat.","module_name":"default-filesystem-subtree-limit-budget","package_name":"default-filesystem-subtree-limit-budget","function_definitions":{"default-filesystem-subtree-limit-budget":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"budget","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":5000},{"instruction_type":"return_statement","return_payload":{"value":"budget"}}]}}}